<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Whenever a method requires a specific data model element type to be set in the call, the type should be enforced.</p>

<p>For instance, calling $entry-&gt;setTitle requires that a Zend_Gdata_App_Extension_Title be used.  However, if you set a simple string, everything works with the set, but when saveXML or getDOM gets called, it's difficult to determine what failed-- because something like 'Call to a member function getDOM() on a non-object ...*' is thrown.</p>

    </div>
